==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Conflation
<hw>Con*fla"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>conflatio</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A blowing together, as of
many instruments in a concert, or of many fires in a foundry.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark> <rj><au>Bacon.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>a fusing together; merger of two or more things or
ideas into one.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Conflict</ent>⟦br⟧
